---
layout: base
title: "A Living World"
description: "The living lore encyclopedia for Ahvantir — the great city of Aru'Mas and the world beyond."
---

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero__inner">
    <p class="hero__eyebrow">The Lore Encyclopedia of</p>
    <h1 class="hero__title">Ahvantir</h1>
    <p class="hero__subtitle">A world shaped by ancient pacts, layered histories,<br>and the city that never sleeps — <em>Aru'Mas</em>.</p>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a href="/articles/" class="btn btn--primary">Browse Articles</a>
      <a href="/search/" class="btn btn--ghost">Search the Records</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero__deckle" aria-hidden="true"></div>
</section>

<section class="home-intro">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="ornament" aria-hidden="true"><span class="ornament__symbol">✦</span></div>
    <div class="home-intro__text">
      <p>
        These records belong to the Aru'Mas Historical Society — compiled from guild archives,
        temple manuscripts, noble house memoirs, and accounts recovered from the ruins of older ages.
        What follows is not a complete history. It is what survived.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ahvantir is a world of deliberate complexity: heroic founders who committed atrocities,
        gods who may be tyrants, and a city where every district keeps its own secrets.
        Read carefully. Not all sources agree.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-categories">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Browse by Subject</h2>
    <div class="category-grid">
      {% for cat in meta.categories %}
      <a href="/articles/#{{ cat.slug }}" class="category-card">
        <span class="category-card__icon" aria-hidden="true">{{ cat.icon }}</span>
        <h3 class="category-card__title">{{ cat.label }}</h3>
        <p class="category-card__desc">{{ cat.description }}</p>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% if collections.allArticles.length %}
<section class="home-recent">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="ornament" aria-hidden="true"><span class="ornament__symbol">✦</span></div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Recent Articles</h2>
    <div class="article-grid">
      {% set recentArticles = collections.allArticles | reverse %}
      {% for article in recentArticles %}
      {% if loop.index <= 6 %}
      <a href="{{ article.url }}" class="article-card">
        {% if article.data.category %}
        <span class="article-card__cat">{{ article.data.category | capitalize }}</span>
        {% endif %}
        <h3 class="article-card__title">{{ article.data.title }}</h3>
        {% if article.data.description %}
        <p class="article-card__desc">{{ article.data.description }}</p>
        {% endif %}
      </a>
      {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="home-recent__more">
      <a href="/articles/" class="btn btn--ghost">View All Articles</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}
